<item>
            <title>[LU-17002] kernel update [RHEL7.9 3.10.0-1160.95.1.el7]</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17002</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Security Fix(es):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: use-after-free caused by l2cap_reassemble_sdu() in&lt;br/&gt;
net/bluetooth/l2cap_core.c (CVE-2022-3564)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Bug Fix(es):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;perf record -ag does not capture user space stack frames on s390x&lt;br/&gt;
(BZ#2207745)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;RHEL7.9 - kernel: handle new reply code FILTERED_BY_HYPERVISOR&lt;br/&gt;
(BZ#2212672)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://listman.redhat.com/archives/rhsa-announce/2023-July/012476.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://listman.redhat.com/archives/rhsa-announce/2023-July/012476.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
Kernel 3.10.0-1160.92.1.el7 update also fixes the following bugs:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;iscsi target deadlocks when the same host acts as an initiator to itself (i.e. connects via 127.0.0.1). (BZ#2181931)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Running LTP testcase setsock09 causes system hang &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;7.9.z&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;. (BZ#2182642)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;ESXi Broadwell cpu show retbleed affected on vmware guest &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;7.9.z&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;. (BZ#2189556)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHBA-2023:3484&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHBA-2023:3484&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
